webpackJsonp([0xb6d7e34efa073000],{"./node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/mathematics-circle-equations.json":function(e,r){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<h2>Circle Equations</h2>\n<p><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pranabendra/articles/master/geometry/circle/circle_2.gif" alt="Circle centered at (x0, y0) with radius r, a point P(x, y) on the circle, and angle t"></p>\n<h3>1. Centre-radius form:</h3>\n<p>Circle having centre <i><b>(x<sub>0</sub>, y<sub>0</sub>)</b></i> and radius <b><i>r</i></b>.</p>\n<p>The equation of the circle can be represented as:</p>\n<p><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pranabendra/articles/master/geometry/circle/circle_3.png" alt="(x-x0)^2 + (y-y0)^2 = r^2"></p>\n<h4>General Equation of a Circle:</h4>\n<p><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pranabendra/articles/master/geometry/circle/circle_6.png" alt="x^2 + y^2 + 2gx + 2fy + c = 0"></p>\n<p>where, <code>g</code>, <code>f</code>, and <code>c</code> are constants.</p>\n<p>Therefore,</p>\n<p><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pranabendra/articles/master/geometry/circle/circle_9.png" alt="x0 = (-g), y0 = (-f), and r = square root of (g^2 + f^2 -c)"></p>\n<h3>2. Parametric form:</h3>\n<p>Circle having centre <i><b>(x<sub>0</sub>, y<sub>0</sub>)</b></i> and radius makes an angle <b><i>t</i></b> with the positive direction of <i>x-axis</i>, then <b><i>t</i></b> is called the <code>parameter</code>.</p>\n<p>The equation of the circle can be represented as:</p>\n<p><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pranabendra/articles/master/geometry/circle/circle_4.png" alt="x = x0 + rcos(t), y = y0 + rsin(t)"></p>\n<p>for, </p>\n<p><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pranabendra/articles/master/geometry/circle/circle_5.png" alt="0<=t<= 2 pi"></p>\n<h3>More Information:</h3>\n<p><a href = "http://mypages.valdosta.edu/alazari/math1111/Circle.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Equation of a Circle</a></p>',fields:{slug:"/mathematics/circle-equations/"},frontmatter:{title:"Circle Equations"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/mathematics/circle-equations/"}}}});
